hja Setiaadmadja Receives Award for Supporting National Stunting Reduction Program"}, {"body": "PT Garuda Indonesia Tbk (GIAA) has made a significant financial turnaround under CEO Irfan Setiaputra's leadership, reducing short-term liabilities by 30.69% to USD 1.16 billion and improving asset deficiency by 16.48% to USD 1.28 billion, while posting a net profit of USD 250 million in 2023. The airline's total operating revenues also grew 39.80% to USD 2.93 billion, driven by a 41% increase in scheduled flights, and has implemented environmentally-friendly initiatives that have led to a reduction of 26.1 tons of plastic waste and 65.2 tons of carbon emissions per year.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 2, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 1, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "transportation-logistic", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51454/irfan-setiaputra-named-ceo-tempo-idnfinancials", "sub_sector": ["transportation"], "tags": ["Earnings Report", "Executive Changes", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Financial Ratios", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["GIAA.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-15T16:14:00", "title": "Garuda Indonesia's CEO Irfan Setiaputra receives \"Best CEO\" award for inspirational leadership and financial turnaround during the COVID-19 pandemic."}, {"body": "The Top CEO Indonesia Awards 2024 recognized 51 CEOs from large-cap companies across various industries, with a combined market capitalization of IDR 7.46 quadrillion as of August 2024, for their exceptional performance in driving growth in assets, equity, revenue, and net profits while implementing sustainability initiatives. The awardees, including 10 CEOs from top 10 market capitalization companies on the Indonesia Stock Exchange, were selected for their dedication to social responsibility and tangible positive impact on environmental, social, and community programs.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 1, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51453/tempo-idn-financials-releases-list-ceos", "sub_sector": ["holding-investment-companies"], "tags": ["IDX", "Executive Changes", "ESG", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-11-15T11:41:15", "title": "Tempo-IDN Financials Unveils List of Top 51 CEOs in Indonesia for 2024"}, {"body": "PT Indal Aluminium Industry Tbk (INAI) has granted IDR 102 billion in extra capital to its subsidiary, PT Indalex, to reduce the latter's debt expenses and lower interest expenses in its financial report. The move, approved during a general meeting of Indalex shareholders in July 2024, will not change the controlling shareholder position of Indalex, with INAI and Indal Investindo holding 99.99% stakes in both companies as of September 30, 2024.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 1, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51451/indal-alumunium-industry-inject-subsidiary-idr-refinancing", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["Debt", "Interest Rates", "Financial Ratios", "Balance Sheets", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["INAI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-14T14:44:01", "title": "PT Indal Aluminium Industry Grants IDR 102 Billion in Extra Capital to Subsidiary PT Indalex to Reduce Debt Expenses."}, {"body": "Individual investors, including Siauw Yunus Subandi and Fitradityo Harjuno, acquired significant stakes in various Indonesian companies, such as PT Graha Andrasentra Propertindo Tbk (JGLE) and PT Nusatama Berkah Tbk, respectively, while PT Trimegah Sekuritas Indonesia Tbk increased its ownership in PT Indomobil Sukses Internasional Tbk. Meanwhile, PT MNC Sekuritas reduced its stake in PT MNC Land Tbk, and foreign investors, including Gochean Holdings Incorporated and Salween Investment Pte Ltd, sold shares in PT Triputra Agro Persada Tbk.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51450/siauw-yunus-owns-jungle-series-jgle-purchasing-shares", "sub_sector": ["consumer-services", "industrial-goods", "investment-service", "retailing", "consumer-services", "food-beverage"], "tags": ["IDX", "Mergers & Acquisitions", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["JGLE.JK", "NTBK.JK", "TRIM.JK", "IMAS.JK", "KPIG.JK", "TAPG.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-14T13:40:51", "title": "Individual investors and securities firms make notable transactions in Indonesian companies, including Jungle Series amusement park and coal mining industry."}, {"body": "Foreign investors sold a net 996.41 million shares, driven by sales of PT Goto Gojek Tokopedia Tbk (GOTO) shares, which reached 1.43 billion shares, and PT Bumi Resources Tbk (BUMI) shares, which totaled 633.30 million shares. Meanwhile, foreign investors bought shares of companies such as PT Darma Henwa Tbk (DEWA), PT Buana Lintas Lautan Tbk (BULL), and PT Bank KB Bukopin Tbk (BBKP), with net volumes ranging from 13.60 million to 190.97 million shares.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "technology", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51449/foreign-sell-recorded-higher-foreign-volume-drops-shares", "sub_sector": ["software-it-services", "basic-materials", "oil-gas-coal", "oil-gas-coal", "oil-gas-coal", "banks"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["GOTO.JK", "BRMS.JK", "BUMI.JK", "DEWA.JK", "BULL.JK", "BBKP.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-14T11:20:58", "title": "Foreign investors sell more shares than they buy in Indonesian market, led by sales of digital company GoTo and coal miner Bumi Resources."}, {"body": "Foreign investors bought a net 279.49 million shares on Tuesday, November 12, with top purchases including PT Bumi Resources Tbk (BUMI) at 1.94 billion shares, PT Darma Henwa Tbk (DEWA) at 269.13 million shares, and PT Buana Lintas Lautan Tbk (BULL) at 66.31 million shares. Meanwhile, top sales included PT Goto Gojek Tokopedia Tbk (GOTO) at 1.79 billion shares, PT Bumi Resources Minerals Tbk (BRMS) at 607.98 million shares, and PT Telkom Indonesia Tbk (TLKM) at 175.85 million shares.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51448/foreign-exceeds-shares-foreign-volume-closed-shares", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal", "oil-gas-coal", "oil-gas-coal", "software-it-services", "basic-materials", "telecommunication"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["BUMI.JK", "DEWA.JK", "BULL.JK", "GOTO.JK", "BRMS.JK", "TLKM.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-14T11:18:27", "title": "Foreign investors buy 279.49 million shares in Indonesian market, led by coal mining and general mining contractor services companies."}, {"body": "PT Petrosea Tbk (PTRO) has established a new subsidiary, PT Lintas Kelola Berlaba (LKB), through its existing subsidiary PT Petrosea Infrastruktur Nusantara, with an authorized capital of IDR 20 billion and issued paid-up capital of IDR 5 billion, to engage in mining services and professional activities. PTRO, through PT Petrosea Infrastruktur Nusantara, controls 51% of LKB's shares, while PT Pasir Bara Prima holds the remaining 49%, as part of PTRO's expansion strategy in the mining services sector.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 1, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51447/petrosea-form-subsidiary-mining-services-industry", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["PTRO.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-14T10:28:22", "title": "PT Petrosea Tbk Establishes New Subsidiary to Engage in Mining Services and Technical Activities."}, {"body": "PT Sat Nusapersada Tbk (PTSN) has secured a $53.5 million credit facility from PT Bank Mandiri Tbk (BMRI), comprising a $45 million investment credit, $4 million working capital credit, and $4.5 million treasury line credit. The credit facility will support the company's business developments, including a new building construction project, and help pay off existing debt, ultimately increasing the company's financial liquidity.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "technology", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51441/sat-nusapersada-secures-credit-facility-bank-mandiri", "sub_sector": ["technology-hardware-equipment", "banks"], "tags": ["Debt", "Bonds", "Interest Rates", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["PTSN.JK", "BMRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-13T13:55:47", "title": "PT Sat Nusapersada obtains $53.5 million credit facility from PT Bank Mandiri to support business developments and debt repayment."}, {"body": "PT JASUINDO TIGA PERKASA TBK (JTPE) will distribute an interim dividend of IDR 47.96 billion, or IDR 7 per share, to its shareholders, following approval from the company's board of directors and commissioners. The company reported a net profit of IDR 119.64 billion for the first nine months of 2024 and had retained earnings of IDR 794.56 billion as of September 30, 2024.", "dimension": {"dividend": 2, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "industrials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51440/jtpe-distribute-interim-dividend-idr", "sub_sector": ["industrial-services"], "tags": ["Dividends", "IDX", "Earnings Report", "Financial Ratios", "Balance Sheets", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["JTPE.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-11-13T11:45:18", "title": "PT Jasuindo Tiga Perkasa to Distribute IDR 47.96 Billion Interim Dividend to Shareholders"}, {"body": "PT Samuel International is investing IDR 482.48 billion in PT MD Entertainment Tbk (MDEN) through a private placement of 170.24 million shares at IDR 2,834 per share, with proceeds to be used to promote the company's group activities and pursue business expansion. The private placement will increase PT MD Entertainment Tbk's issued and paid-up capital to IDR 989.77 billion from IDR 972.75 billion, with PT Samuel International holding 99.74% of the shares.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51439/samuel-international-inject-capital-film", "sub_sector": ["holding-investment-companies"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-11-13T10:00:01", "title": "PT Samuel International invests IDR 482.48 billion in PT MD Entertainment through private placement of 170.24 million shares."}]